article.description: Marreon Jackson had 26 points as Toledo easily defeated Eastern Michigan 79-57 on Friday night.
article.headline: Jackson scores 26 to carry Toledo over E. Michigan 79-57
article.linkText: Jackson scores 26 to carry Toledo over E. Michigan 79-57
article.story: TOLEDO, Ohio -- Marreon Jackson had 26 points as Toledo easily defeated Eastern Michigan 79-57 on Friday night. Spencer Littleson had 19 points for Toledo (16-15, 8-10 Mid-American Conference). Willie Jackson added 16 points, 15 rebounds and seven assists. Luke Knapke had 16 points, 12 rebounds and three assists. Yeikson Montero had 12 points for the Eagles (16-15, 6-12). Thomas Binelli added 12 points. Boubacar Toure, who was second on the Eagles in scoring coming into the matchup with 11 points per game, shot only 20% for the game (1 of 5). The Rockets evened the season series against the Eagles with the win. Eastern Michigan defeated Toledo 61-57 on Feb. 1. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
